Temp-name '1-punto' refers to first seedling leaf which is unlobed and acuminate.  Seeds and fruits that match those that produce '1-punto' seedlings (plantulas) are assigned this code.  Fruits are ~ 3 cm long in a loose cluster. Adult leaves are shallowly 3-lobed.

Temp-name '5-puntos' refers to first seedling leaf which is 5-lobed. Seeds and fruits matching those that produce '5-puntos' seedlings (plantulas) are assigned this code. Fruits are 4-5 cm long & solitary. Adults leaves are deeply 5-lobed and somewhat glabrous. Adult voucher awaiting ID.
Need to distinguish from CAYA_C.  No adult voucher yet available for identification. Seeds only available on a card voucher.

Temp-name '3-puntos' refers to first seedling leaf which is 3-lobed. Seeds and fruits that match those that produce '3-puntos' seedlings (plantulas) are assigned this code.  Fruits are ~ 3 cm long and tightly clustered. Adult leaves are deeply 5-7 lobed.

Calyptranthes nervata M.L. Kawas. & B. Holst was separated from Calyptranthes plicata in 2009. They are very similar vegetatively.  It is currently unclear which species is represented by these sparse records.
Calyptranthes yasuniana was newly described in 2015 and appears as such in plot list from 2018. It was known as Calyptranthes 'sedosa' in plots lists 2001-2014.
It is Eugenia 'smedbrosimoid' in plot lists 2014-1018.  It was Eugenia aff. dittocrepis O. Berg in plot lists 2009-2010.
Myrciaria racemosa was newly described in 2011 and appears in plot lists 2014-2018.  It appeared as Plinia 'cortezablanca' in earlier plot lists.

The plot lists of 2014-2018 use Pouteria cuspidata (POUTRB) without subspecies.  P. cuspidata subsp. robusta (Mart. & Eichler) T.D. Penn. and P. cuspidata subsp. dura (Eyma) T.D. Penn. occur region and possibly on the plot. Our records are from one tree near trap 155.  The plot code of POUTRB suggests that this is subspecies robusta.

The plot lists of 2014-2018 include both subspecies of Pouteria durlandi as POUTDU. Two subspecies were recognized in the plot list of 2009. Our records are mainly from a single tree at trap 98 that was identified as subsp. durlandii.

Two subspecies of Pouteria torta (Mart.) Radlk. are included as POUTU in plot lists 2014-2018. The two subspecies are recognized in in the plot list of 2009 and plot book (2014).  As our field team notes that the fruit and leaves are very different we distinguish the subspecies in our study.

Two subspecies of Pouteria torta (Mart.) Radlk. are included as POUTU in plot lists 2014-2018. The two subspecies are recognized in in the plot list of 2009 and plot book (2014).  As our field team notes that the fruit and leaves are very different we distinguish the subspecies in our study.

All records are from trap 185. The corresponding card voucher is from tree 450347 near trap 185. This tree is now identified as Elaeoluma glabrescens (Mart. & Eichler) Aubrév. (ELA2GL).  We need to confim whether there is also a SARCSM tree near 195.

Identified to genus by the fruits. No adult vouchers are yet available for comparison. This was originally identifed as Schlegelia spruceana Bureau & K. Schum.  Because that is a Guyanan shield species it is unlikely to be the correct identification.  Seeds of this species are very tiny. Garwood suspects they were possibly mixed with tiny seeds of Philodendron or other species.

Three varieties of Siparuna thecaphora were initially distinguished on the plot as separate taxa in early plot lists (2000). All are now treated as one taxon (SIPATT) on the plot. Only variety 't-stelae' was found in traps (not variety 't-estrellita' or 't-hairy').
Adult voucher awaiting ID.

This code includes unidentified Solanaceae parts (mostly seeds) that were initially recorded initially by trap number (as SOLxx where xx is the trap number).  The saved samples could not be morphologically distinguished or asigned to existing codes.
Adult voucher awaiting ID.  This was previously misidentified as Solanum pensile Sendtn.

Some specimens in the Yasuni field herbarum are annotated as Coussapoa villosa Poepp. & Endl. This is an accepted species name. Garwood is not certain that this name applies to the samples in our traps.

Two subspecies of Pourouma tomentosa Mart. ex Miq. are combined into a single code (POURTO) in the plot lists of 2018 & 2014.  They were considered separate taxa in the plot lists of 2001-2010.  We use the two subspecies as they are recognized taxa.

Isolated seeds. Probably an error and equal VRB_PA.  Garwood has no records of this code in collection database.
Isolated seeds matched to seeds on a seedling provisionally identified as Verbenaceae.  Possibly equal VER_C.

Two varieties of Leonia glycycarpa Ruiz & Pav. (var. glycycarpa Ruiz & Pav. and var. racemosa (Mart.) L.B. Sm. & Á. Fernández) are treated as one taxon in the plot lists of 2014-2018.  The two varitieis were distinguished in the plot lists of 2009-2010. Both varieties are known in region.  The traps contain only var. glycyarpa.
